text:
Cyrtophora cicatrosa - the tent-web spider.
Cyrtophora, the tent-web spiders, is a genus of orb-weaver spiders. Although they are in the "orb weaver" family, they do not build orb webs. Their tent-like, highly complex non-sticky web is sometimes considered a precursor of the simplified orb web. These webs are aligned horizontally, with a network of supporting threads above them. These spiders often. live in colonies.
Home Garden, Khar West, Mumbai.

text:
This beautiful Lynx Spider was sighted and photographed here at Pollachi outskirts, during the month of January 2021. This is a handheld focus stack of 10 images. I really love stacking these spiders as they sit still and pose for us. Yet, the hard part is correctly stacking the hairs and thorny parts of the spider. Its very hard that sometimes they misalign. Even a slightest movement makes it ugly after stacking, which destroys the images altogether. Hope you all do like this image. 😊
.
.
Pollachi, Tamilnadu, India.
January 2021.
.
.

text:
Here in the frame, its the beautiful "Adanson's House Jumper (Hasarius adansoni)" female. Recently I dwelled into making diy diffuser more seriously. I made a pretty bigger one and in combination with package foam and tracing paper, I got some quality results. Previously I was using styrofoam sheets. So, this image was shot yesterday while testing my diffuser. I am really happy with the results. I found this really co-operative Jumping Spider in my home and made her my model for the day. Hope you all like the diffusion and the image too. 😊
.
.
Pollachi, Tamilnadu, India.
November 2021.
.
.

text:
Here in the frame, its the beautiful "Adanson's House Jumper (Hasarius adansoni)" female. Recently I dwelled into making diy diffuser more seriously. I made a pretty bigger one and in combination with package foam and tracing paper, I got some quality results. Previously I was using styrofoam sheets. So, this image was shot yesterday while testing my diffuser. I am really happy with the results. I found this really co-operative Jumping Spider in my home and made her my model for the day. Hope you all like the diffusion and the image too. 😊
.
.
Pollachi, Tamilnadu, India.
November 2021.
.
.

text:
The Tribal Spider.
The Hamadruas Spider. Hamataliva.
All of us started our trail the next morning post tea to the nearby spot behind our stay.
For the month of March there was high activity of spiders, predators hunting for their prey.
While we were searching for our subjects, we noticed something move on the bark of a tree.
Behold my first photo of this beautiful tribal design
The Hamadruas Spider. the color and patterns looks like the spider has put on its war colors and is war ready.
MPE 65mm at 3x.
March 21.
Pune, Maharashtra, India.
